JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 150
EP  - 159
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article explores some approaches for designing parametric equations for computerized business gaming models. Details related to the problems associated with developing and quantifying the relationships which are to exist between participant decisions and operating results are presented. The author describes possibilities for decreasing returns curves. A discussion is presented about methods available to increase in returns relationships. The benefits of business games to organizational success are outlined.
AB  - The article explores some approaches for designing parametric equations for computerized business gaming models. Details related to the problems associated with developing and quantifying the relationships which are to exist between participant decisions and operating results are presented. The author describes possibilities for decreasing returns curves. A discussion is presented about methods available to increase in returns relationships. The benefits of business games to organizational success are outlined.
