TY  - JOUR
T1  - Discussion:  Queuing Theory Re-visited
AU  - Zelnick, Joel
Y1  - 1963/06/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254848
DO  - 10.5465/254848
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 173
EP  - 173
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the queuing theory in management. The author explains the importance of understanding the limitations of queuing analysis and its effects on the management of an organization. Details related to the complexity of the solution of queuing problems are presented. The author presents an analysis of the development of general-purpose queuing simulators and their use in maximizing the efficiency of industrial operations. The author also mentions the importance of the relationship between supervisors and their employees for organizational effectiveness.
