PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article focuses on Australia's venture into providing education in administration and management at the university postgraduate level. A discussion is presented about the attitudes of universities in Australia toward the teaching of administration and management and the country's role in the international business community. The author analyzes the amount of interest in the emergence of faculties of commerce and economics at Australian universities. A comparison of Australian and British management education programs is presented.
