TY  - JOUR
T1  - II. Cross-Cultural Perspectives on Management Principles
AU  - Oberg, Winston
Y1  - 1963/06/01
PY  - 1963
DA  - 1963/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254843
DO  - 10.5465/254843
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 129
EP  - 143
VL  - 6
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents information on a survey of management problems among groups of businessmen from Rio Grande do Sul, Brazil and Michigan. The author presents a comparison of the problems perceived by the two sets of managers and offers solutions to each set based on cultural aspects particular to each group. A discussion is presented about the differences in the business climate and situations that exist between Brazil and Michigan. An overview of cultural differences affecting international business is presented.
