N2  - The article discusses selected materials from the psychological and sociological literature which illustrate disagreement in the areas of management and organization. The author describes an investigation of the role of human versus simulated brains in creative leadership. A discussion is presented about the presence of two distinguishable approaches to the human mind in behavioral science literature. An overview of the psychological and sociological aspects of management and organization is presented.
